@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Guide";
}
<div id="guide">
    <h1 style="padding-top: 30px;">How to Use MobileBgWatch</h1>
    <ol>
        <li>
            Go to <a href="https://www.mobile.bg/search/avtomobili-dzhipove" target="_blank">Mobile.bg</a> and select your desired filters. After that, click on Search.
            <br />
            <img src="~/images/guide-img-1.png" alt="Mobile.bg search filters" />
        </li>

        <li>
            Copy the generated link, paste it in the search box on the Home page and click Add. Wait for the program to go through all pages of the search link and collect all vehicles.
            <br />
            <img src="~/images/guide-img-2.png" alt="Copy and paste link" />
        </li>

        <li>
            If everything went well, you should see the first 40 vehicles on the front page for each search link.
            <br />
            <img src="~/images/guide-img-3.png" alt="First 40 vehicles displayed" />
        </li>
        <li>
            When you open the vehicle page, you can see all the relevant information, including price history.
            <br />
            <img src="~/images/guide-img-4.png" alt="Vehicle page with price history" />
        </li>

        <li>
            There is also a Favorites page where you can add or remove vehicles by pressing the heart icon.
            <br />
            <img src="~/images/guide-img-5.png" alt="Favorites page" />
        </li>
    </ol>
    <h2>Additional Information</h2>
    <div class="info" style="font-size: 25px;">
        <ul>
            <li>The site will check for new vehicle ads every 15 minutes and every hour it will perform a full search and update the database.</li>
            <li>Users will receive a message to refresh the page when new ads are found. They can also decide if they want to receive emails with the relevant new ads.</li>
            <li>Users can manually refresh a search link. Each refresh has a 15-minute cooldown.</li>
            <li>The rest of the features you can check for yourself.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

</div>